16. Death. The exact date of ‹Juvenal’s death cannot be determined. We have seen that he was writing as late as the year 128; if we may accept as well founded the tradition in several of the vitae that he lived to bc eighty or more years of age, his decease may be placed in the latter half of the next decade (135-140).

17. Knowledge of philosophy. Though the poems os Juvenal do not furnish much information with regard to the life of their author, they do offer a substantial basis on which to form an estimate of his mental equipment and of some aspects of his character. In the first place, his philo- sophical knowledge is of the most elementary kind.
